- cs.IT (Information Theory) is likely because the paper discusses the use of non-linear families of ternary codes for encoding data into DNA. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is possible because DNA based storage systems may have security implications. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is possible because DNA based storage systems can be considered as a type of database. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is possible because the paper may discuss the computational complexity of encoding and decoding data in DNA based storage systems.
